entries.title: U.S. to Train Ukrainian Troops on Patriot Missile at Oklahoma Base
entries.description: The troops will begin abbreviated training on the air-defense system as soon as next week.

entries.title: Saudi Arabia Considers $11 Billion Lifeline for Pakistan
entries.description: The new assistance could strengthen Pakistan’s hand in negotiating a restart to a bailout from the International Monetary Fund as the country faces default.

entries.title: Brazilian Investigators Home In on Suspects in Riot Financing
entries.description: Officials probe the powerful agribusiness sector for links to a mob that ransacked government buildings in Brasília.

entries.title: World Bank Cuts 2023 Global Growth Projection as Inflation Persists
entries.description: Price pressures raise the risk of global recession at a time when China and Ukraine inject uncertainty into the world economy.

entries.title: Prince Harry's Memoir Is Released, Detailing Deep Royal Rift
entries.description: The book lays bare the scale of the split in the House of Windsor, in an account that royal commentators say could do lasting damage to both the prince and the world’s most famous royal institution.

entries.title: Biden, López Obrador, Trudeau Reach Deals on Chips, Climate, Immigration
entries.description: North American leaders say they will work on boosting semiconductor industries, improving asylum process.

entries.title: Russia Gains Ground in East Ukraine as Fight for Bakhmut Intensifies
entries.description: Russian troops and members of the Wagner Group paramilitary force most likely control the majority of Soledar as they continue efforts to encircle nearby Bakhmut.

entries.title: Macron to Forge Ahead With Contested Pension Overhaul
entries.description: The plan to raise France’s retirement age risks sparking a new wave of protests in the country, where tensions have been simmering for months because of rising food and fuel prices.

entries.title: China Bars South Korean Visitors in Response to Covid-19 Rules
entries.description: Beijing suspended issuing several types of short-term visas in its first retaliation measure over travel restrictions many countries have imposed on flights from China.

entries.title: Brazil's Former President Jair Bolsonaro, in Florida, Accused of Provoking Rioters Back Home
entries.description: President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva blamed his conservative predecessor after a mob of his supporters attacked the capital.
